http.html:
Skip to content

TRAVELLING TYPE II's

CALLING ALL VW BUSES!

  • Home

  • ELKWOOD IIII Sept 2019

Scroll down to content

Welcome to the Travelling Type II’s!!! We are a friendly VW Bus movement that can be found on the open road or campsite in and around the Canadian Rockies Mountains shared between Alberta to British Columbia and Beyond.

ABOUT US

 

The Travelling Type II’s is a non-profit VW Bus camping movement that hosts 3 VW bus camping events every year, Our main event that attracts VW Buses from all over world is CAMPER JAM CANADA  The Jam is held every Canadian August long in Golden, BC. As well we host 2 smaller VW Bus campouts, the Adventure in the late spring and Elkwood in the fall. 

 

CAMPER JAM CANADA AUG 1-5 2019

OH IT’S HAPPENING!!   SEE YOU THEN JAMMERS!!!

ADVENTURE IIIII 2019

ADVENTURE IIIII 2019

The campers have voted 5th year in a row!! The Travelling Type II’s are returning to the beautiful Kikomun Provincial Park for Adventure IIIII You have 2 options of Adventure to chose from either 2 night or 3 night Adventure IIIII June 21st-24th Mon-Fri. The Adventure IIIII cruise will start in Calgary at Canadian Tire Shawnessy SW Friday time will TBD as a group and we will connect with everyone that is going. We will stop in the Crow nest pass Tim Hortons for food & fuel than continue onto to another favorite stop Fernie Brewing Co. to fill up the growers and coolers for the weekend. The ADVENTURE IIIII will continue to the private picturesque almost lake side spot. Where we will chill and soak up the sunshine have a great weekend camping, see you there folks!! THERE’s only room for 30 VW Buses 😉

GOOGLE MAPS: DIRECTIONS

APPLE MAPS: DIRECTIONS DO NOT DRIVE INTO THE WATER, GROUP CAMPSITE @ END OF ROAD

Greetings from the Park County Radio Club

Welcome to the Park County Radio Club (PCRC) website. Park County is approximately 2,200 square miles located in Central Colorado. The geographic center of Colorado is located within Park County and includes the famous South Park and 4 of Colorado’s 14er mountains. 

The club maintains 2 mountain top repeaters that provide coverage in about 75% of the county.  The club participates in various community events and activities and provides many training and fun activities for its members.  Please explore our other pages for more information and details.

Dan Kern – WØDFU
Park County Radio Club President

Upcoming Events

PCRC ARISS EVENT

CONTACT – The ISS contact was very succesful this morning with the exception of the You Tube live feed which did not work. We had about 9 minutes and the kids did a great job asking their questions. Thanks to al the voluteers and sponsors who made this happen.

There will be a news story on Channel 4 Denver at 5 PM tonight. If you don’t get channel 4, it will be on their website later this evening.

There will aslo be a videos and pictures posted on the PCRC website later after the are edited.
